ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredName: PBSC CD34+ cell Harvest Procedure Performed
Property.preferredDefinition: Immature cells found circulating in the bloodstream. New blood cells develop from peripheral stem cells.:No value exists.:Harvest; remove from a culture or a living or dead body, as for the purposes of transplantation.:Performed; carried out.

Concepts.definition: An immature (progenitor) cell circulating in the peripheral blood.  It has the capacity for replication and differentiation to mature blood cells.
Remove from a culture or a living or dead body, as for the purposes of transplantation.
Executed and carried through to completion.
